height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/AnrrecV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[njdhytr]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Brooke may have some disabilities but it’s doesn’t stop her from living a life full of joy!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pWvi5bs</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cDp4K1D.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4vd6THJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>NTBD, but I would die for Brooke!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pWvi5bs</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tampacl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The American love of Ice Cream</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Gy4G1qL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5OLncWP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Moar info: https://www.military.com/history/why-us-navy-operated-fleet-of-ice-cream-ships-during-world-war-ii.html

Though Prohibition, which outlawed the manufacture and sale of alcohol in the United States, ended before the start of World War II, American industry needed to make products to fill the gaps booze left behind. More than one beer brewery converted its machinery to make ice cream, and soda fountains replaced saloons as gathering spots. Between 1916 and 1925, ice cream consumption grew by 55% among hungry Americans.

At the beginning of World War II, the American ice cream factory was far removed from the labor-intensive, salt-and-ice operations of the 19th century. The consumer could buy ice cream at more outlets and in a greater variety of flavors and packages than ever before.

Neither the end of Prohibition nor the Great Depression could stop the American ice-cream craze. So when the country entered World War II, it naturally became what we call today a "force multiplier."

The U.S. Navy had (in)famously outlawed alcohol aboard ships in 1914, six years before Prohibition, but it still needed to fill the gap in morale boosting power a sailors daily drink left behind. As any noncommissioned officer who has overseen junior enlisted Americans will tell you: if you don't give them something to boost their morale, they can get into anything ... and you might not like what they find.

video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OigDDVn3IaU</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Gy4G1qL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[psuedon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Viper – Doomsday (2008)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1RmUux3</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sulQcrP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Stuntwoman and actress Lee-Anne Liebenberg portrays Viper, a commander from a society of savages in a post-apocalyptic Scotland</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ud6xsm9.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Set 27 years after Scotland was quarantined due to a virus, the film follows a force led by Eden Sinclair (Rhona Mitra) that enters the forbidden zone to find a cure</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Q5Etz1Z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This UK sci fi by Neil Marshall (Dog Soldiers, The Descent) unfortunately blends far more inspirations than it can handle, trading coherency and credibility for fast-cut spectacle</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Yc11UJk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Its great cast (including Bob Hoskins, Malcolm McDowell, Alexander Siddig, Craig Conway, etc) has little to work with, yet there are still interesting elements</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/N1UpJjS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>One of these is obviously the fell and styled up warrior who would have made the ancient Picts proud, or at least Sawney Bean</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/naVX2oz.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Despite a limited role was Viper elevated to the icon of the flick and is on many posters and covers</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zj1VeJc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It is the best known acting role of Lee-Anne Liebenberg. As a stuntwoman she has credits as performer/double, coordinator, fight choreographer, and precision driver</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/p3pPbf0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Among the films she worked on are Avengers: Age of Ultron, Chappie, and District 9</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lQ5Gts9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1RmUux3</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ngugi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>They're eating the pets ! They're eating the cats ! I'm not sure, look :</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ACXmDkJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c4L3SOV.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4AL6qNB.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2 :: Finally eating</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FSKpH3q.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Rooooky !</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vrawr7R.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>4 :: what is that foam, mate ??</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tDSMPbQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Good job my cat !</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4bbifnR.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>6 :: A good catcher cat</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/evr5Wwl.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Mesmerizing cat pull-up</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IybwPZm.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><d